\sum\limits_{k=1}^n\frac{2k+1}{k(k+1)}
\sum u\Delta v=uv-\sum Ev\Delta u
u = 2x+1, \Delta v=1/x(x+1)=(x-1)_{-2}
v=-(x-1)_{-1}=-1/x
\Delta u = 2, Ev = -1/(x+1)
\sum\frac{(2x+1)}{x(x+1)}\delta x=\frac{-2x-1}{x}+2\left(\sum x_{-1}\delta x\right)
\sum x_{-1}\delta x
\int x^{-1}dx=ln(x)
H_n
 S_n = \sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{1}{k} + \sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{1}{k+1}=2H_n-1+\frac{1}{n+1}=2H_n-\frac{n}{n+1} 
